gomodel:SYNGO_979  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The paper examines the signal transduction pathway where CaMKIalpha is involved.\nSince the end-result of the activation is a change in spine morphology, the authors examine the sub cellular localization of CaMKIalpha, to show that all components of the signaling pathway are located in the same sub cellular compartment.\n\nFigure S7 presents a WB analysis of an isolated PSD fraction and demonstrates a strong signal for CaMKIalpha using a specific antibody.\n\n**Figure 4b: Immunostaining showing the phosphorylated CaMKI is found in dendritic spines in cultured hippocampal neurons. However, the antibody is a 'pCaMKI' and there is no information regarding the isoform of CaMKI that it targets.\n\n2/7/2017 Pim\n- As far as I can see there are not muliple isoforms of CamKI in Uniprot. Therefore, Fig.4b seems useful of annotation of CamKI as well.. Experimental description: 'Medium-density (3.2 × 104 cells per square centimeter) hippocampal neurons were isolated from P0-2 Sprague Dawley rat as described (Wayman et al., 2006).'\nFor figure S7: 'Purified rat PSDs were a gift from Dr. Ayse Dosemeci (NIH).'" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_979" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

